                <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Bloodlich[/i]
[br]<blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">[i]Originally posted by Mebryn[/i]
[br]What's the best way to raise hit points as high as posible? i'm a 54 Nec and only have 1700hp. Should I focus on levelling more? Getting better gear? getting more Sta? or even more HP items? Any suggestions would be great.
[/quote]

I look at it this way.  You'll never get the highiest possible HP's for any character.  I dont care who you are and what type of items your character holds.  You may have 5k to 10k HP's but you will never have the max HP ever.

Maybe thats a "slight" reason why we have this game named "ever"quest. heheh

It dwindles down to how much you have and what you can work with.  If you have 50p, then 50p will get you "what you payed for".  If you have 1700p, then you can get some possible "not the best", but fairly ok gear to work with that will get your HP's up a few 100 possibly.

There are some decent gear out there that you can certainly buy for just 1700p to work with.  Some gear with +50 to +60 bonus points in HP and also STA.

Personally, Id split up your 1700p and get half +HP items, half +STA items to even balance your character out.

Now when you have 6 degit ammount of plat (20k, 50k 100k, etc etc), then well............you do the math.  You will be able to get the big time gear that has over +100 HP and +100 STA bonus.

Its just like buying a car.  If you want to get a nice car with some nice stocked items in it, your going to pay out your rear for it.

Bottom line, the more the meier.
[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
